    "Unknown": "), they sat down in ranks by hundreds and by fifties (\nv. 39); He went again, and prayed, saying, ton auton logon\u2014the same word, or matter, or business; he spoke to the same purport, and again the third time. This teaches us, that men ought to pray, and not to faint, Luke xviii."
